// Go workspace tying the infra/ modules together. Each module ships
// its own go.mod (so the modules can be built / released independently)
// but local development resolves cross-module imports through this
// workspace without each consumer needing a `replace` directive.
//
// macos-host-bootstrap is the substrate the Apple Silicon CAPI
// providers consume. Today only the Scaleway one is wired up; the
// AWS EC2 Mac path described in PR #10499's BYOC section will land
// as a sibling module that imports macos-host-bootstrap unchanged.
//
// tart-kubelet has no dependencies on the others — it ships as a
// binary baked into each provider's controller image.

go 1.25.0

use (
	./infra/cluster-api-provider-scaleway-applesilicon
	./infra/macos-host-bootstrap
	./infra/tart-kubelet
)
